metadata.name: Ockley to Dorking, via Leith Hill Tower
metadata.desc: A lovely ~4 hour walk from Ockley railway station to Dorking, via the beautiful view from Leith Hill Tower.

wpt.name: Ockley Railway Station
wpt.desc: Direct trains from London Victoria leaving (for us, on a Saturday), once every hour taking roughly 1h10.

wpt.name: Leith Hill Tower
wpt.desc: Beautiful views of all of South East England. The Tower (Â£3 entry, card accepted) takes you to the highest point of the SE (and higher than the shard above sea level). Good views even in cloudy weather.

wpt.name: Main road walking
wpt.desc: There's 100m or so walking along a main road's verge without a path. Cars were kind!

wpt.name: The King's Arms
wpt.desc: A lovely pub, in fact the oldest in Dorking, with good food for the end of the hike.

wpt.name: Dorking Railway Station
wpt.desc: Trains left every 15 minutes or so for us (on a Saturday late afternoon), and went direct to London Victoria.

trk.name: Ockley to Dorking, via Leith Hill Tower
